Cheery picked up on top of the master and force pushed to the branch. 
Tested on both local and Yarn. 
@markusweimer could you please merge for me before more conflicts come?

@markusweimer I'll move the 

```
   for (final Class<? extends Name<?>> clazz : c.builder.freeParams.keySet()) 
```

loop to a separate method and test the method. This will help readability as well.

@afchung  I would also like to review this one since I have to use and deal with it in future...Will it be possible for you to:

a) Add comments and documentation in the code.
b) Write a bit of detailed comments in JIRA on how accessing data from azure blob works and all (If there is already a nice documentaiton somewhere please provide a link to it and add it to BlobFileSystem documentation also). For example, what does BlobClient do, and overall flow of implementing AzureFileSystem. I am not sure that except @markusweimer  and probably @beysims  if others know how it works.

@dkm2110 Sure. All public facing APIs are already documented. Let me know if there are sections of the code that isn't intuitive, since most of these calls are just wrappers for the Azure Storage Blob Client. For now, the `AzureBlobFileSystem` isn't particularly efficient because it makes calls such as `GetBlobReferenceFromServer()`.
See http://stackoverflow.com/questions/18053679/what-is-the-difference-between-getblobreference-and-getblobreferencefromserver for why it's not efficient.
I believe, however, there is no `GetBlobFromReference()` method in the Azure Blob Storage API, but instead there are methods such as `GetBlockBlobReference()` and `GetPageBlobReference()`. This, although more efficient than `GetBlobReferenceFromServer()`, will limit us to a single type of blob we can support, so I ultimately chose to use `GetBlobReferenceFromServer()` instead. Do you think we should only support a single type of blob? Or should we be more general.
